To verify correct integration in the chloroplast genome and successful homoplasmy, total DNA was extracted from all transformants with a standard phenol/chloroform extraction protocol (Sambrook and Russell, 2006). Correct integration of plasmid DNA was checked by PCR amplification (

) with the following primers: Chla1-for 5′-ACAACTAAAATTGTTAGTTTCTT-3′ and Chla1-rev 5′-TGC CTCTAATAAAGTCATCG-3′, Chla2-for 5′-TCAAGCACTCATGTGAT TTT-3′ and Chla2-rev 5′-AAAACGAATCCATTACGATTA-3’. Homoplasmy was checked with primers Chla3-for 5′-CACGTTTAACGGCGTC CTTTA-3′ and Chla3-rev 5′-ACTTATCTGATTCAAAAGTA-3′ as showed in 
Fig. 2B
. The expected amplicon sizes were 1.358 bp for Chla1, 2.519 bp for Chla2, and 954 bp for Chla3 amplicons. The presence of amplicons Chla1 and Chla2 indicates correct plasmid integration in the chloroplast genome. The absence of amplicon Chla3 indicates that the transformants are homoplasmic for the presence of the transgene (
Fig. 2B and C
).
